2003-09-3  Sean Middleditch <elanthis@awesomeplay.com>

	* configure.in, Makefile.am, News

	 Quick suggestion for keeping the RPM spec up-to-date (it's got
	the wrong version in 0.7.0) - use the configure script to update it.
	I.e., make conglomerate.spec to conglomerate.spec.in, set the
	version as @VERSION@, and add conglomerate.spec to AC_OUTPUT.
	Then the version is always up-to-date, which is usually all
	that needs changing in a spec file.  ^,^

	* conglomerate.spec.in

	New file

	* conglomerate.spec

	Removed


